  "lesson": {
    "title": "Pot-Controlled LED Threshold",
    "description": "A potentiometer and two 10kΩ resistors form a voltage divider on the transistor base. Turn the pot until the base voltage crosses the switching point — the LED snaps between off and on instead of fading smoothly like lesson 14."
